{"name":"Kender","permission":{"default":0,"fRudea7oGPoV9HaK":3},"type":"race","data":{"description":{"value":"<h2>Starting Age</h2>\n<table style=\"border-spacing: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; margin: 10px; table-layout: fixed; border-color: #888888; min-width: 200px; color: #333333; font-family: Varela, sans-serif;\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<thead style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: #cfe2f3;\">\n<tr style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">\n<th class=\"text\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px; text-align: left; border: 1px solid #888888;\">Adulthood</th>\n<th class=\"text\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px; text-align: left; border: 1px solid #888888;\">Intuitive<span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; position: relative; font-size: 10px; line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; top: -0.5em;\">1</span></th>\n<th class=\"text\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px; text-align: left; border: 1px solid #888888;\">Self-Taught<span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; position: relative; font-size: 10px; line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; top: -0.5em;\">2</span></th>\n<th class=\"text\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px; text-align: left; border: 1px solid #888888;\">Trained<span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; position: relative; font-size: 10px; line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; top: -0.5em;\">3</span></th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">\n<tr style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">\n<td class=\"text\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #888888;\">20 years</td>\n<td class=\"text\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #888888;\">+2d4 years<br style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" />(22 &ndash; 28 years)</td>\n<td class=\"text\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #888888;\">+3d6 years<br style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" />(23 &ndash; 38 years)</td>\n<td class=\"text\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #888888;\">+4d6 years<br style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" />(24 &ndash; 44 years)</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><sup style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\">1</sup><span style=\"color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">&nbsp;This category includes barbarians, oracles, rogues, and sorcerers.</span><br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" /><sup style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\">2</sup><span style=\"color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">&nbsp;This category includes bards, cavaliers, fighters, gunslingers, paladins, rangers, summoners, and witches.</span><br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" /><sup style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\">3</sup><span style=\"color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"> This category includes alchemists, clerics, druids, inquisitors, magi, monks, and wizards.</span></p>\n<h2>Height and Weight</h2>\n<table style=\"border-spacing: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; margin: 10px; table-layout: fixed; border-color: #888888; min-width: 200px; color: #333333; font-family: Varela, sans-serif;\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n<thead style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: #cfe2f3;\">\n<tr style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">\n<th class=\"text\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px; text-align: left; border: 1px solid #888888;\">Gender</th>\n<th class=\"text\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px; text-align: left; border: 1px solid #888888;\">Base Height</th>\n<th class=\"text\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px; text-align: left; border: 1px solid #888888;\">Height Modifier</th>\n<th class=\"text\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px; text-align: left; border: 1px solid #888888;\">Base Weight</th>\n<th class=\"text\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px; text-align: left; border: 1px solid #888888;\">Weight Modifier</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">\n<tr style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">\n<td class=\"text\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #888888;\">Male</td>\n<td class=\"text\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #888888;\">2 ft. 8 in.</td>\n<td class=\"text\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #888888;\">+2d4 in.<br style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" />(2 ft. 10 in. &ndash; 3 ft. 4 in.)</td>\n<td class=\"text\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #888888;\">30 lbs.</td>\n<td class=\"text\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #888888;\">+(2d4 lbs.)<br style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" />(32 &ndash; 38 lbs.)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: #f3f3f3;\">\n<td class=\"text\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #888888;\">Female</td>\n<td class=\"text\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #888888;\">2 ft. 6 in.</td>\n<td class=\"text\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #888888;\">+2d4 in.<br style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" />(2 ft. 8 in. &ndash; 3 ft. 2 in.)</td>\n<td class=\"text\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #888888;\">25 lbs.</td>\n<td class=\"text\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #888888;\">+(2d4 lbs.)<br style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" />(27 &ndash; 33 lbs.)</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h2>Standard Racial Traits</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Ability Score Modifiers</strong>: Halflings are nimble and strong-willed, but their small stature makes them weaker than other races. They gain +2&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Dexterity-Dex-\">Dexterity</a>, +2&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Charisma-Cha-\">Charisma</a>, &ndash;2 <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/cleric/domains/paizo-domains/strength-domain\">Strength</a>, and -2 <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores/#TOC-Wisdom-Wis-\">Wisdom</a>.</li>\n<li><strong>Size</strong>: Kender are Small creatures and gain a +1 <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/glossary#TOC-Size-Bonus\">size bonus</a>&nbsp;to their AC, a +1&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/glossary#TOC-Size-Bonus\">size bonus</a>&nbsp;on&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Attack-Roll\">attack rolls</a>, a &ndash;1 penalty to their&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Combat-Maneuver-Bonus\">CMB</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Combat-Maneuver-Defense\">CMD</a>, and a +4&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/glossary#TOC-Size-Bonus\">size bonus</a>&nbsp;on&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/stealth\">Stealth</a>&nbsp;checks.</li>\n<li><strong>Type</strong>: <a href=\"https://dragonlancenexus.com/kender-pathfinder-conversion/\">Kender</a> are <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/bestiary/rules-for-monsters/creature-types#TOC-Humanoid\">humanoids</a>.</li>\n<li><strong>Base Speed (Slow Speed)</strong>: Halflings have a base speed of 20 feet.</li>\n<li><strong>Languages:</strong> Kender begin play speaking Common and Kenderspeak. Kender with high <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Intelligence-Int-\">Intelligence</a> scores can choose from the following: Dwarven, Ergot, Elven, Goblin, Solamnic.</li>\n<li>See the <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/linguistics\">Linguistics skill page</a>&nbsp;for more information about these languages.</li>\n<li><strong>Fearless:</strong> Kender are immune to fear, both magical and otherwise.</li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 2px 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 15.2px;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 15.2px;\">Kender Luck</strong>: Kender receives a +1 racial bonus on all saving throws. Due to their eternal optimism and inherent belief in the goodness of all people, Kender manages to survive and thrive in a world that is often hostile to them.</li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 2px 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 15.2px;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 15.2px;\">Handler</strong>: Kender has a reputation for larceny and guile&mdash;and sometimes it&rsquo;s well deserved. Kender gain a +2 racial bonus on Disable Device and Sleight of Hand checks, and Sleight of Hand is always a class skill for them.</li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 2px 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 15.2px;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 15.2px;\">Wanderlust:</strong>&nbsp;Kender loves to travel and maps. Kender receives a +2 bonus on Knowledge (geography) and Survival checks.</li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 2px 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 15.2px;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 15.2px;\">Keen Senses</strong>: Kender receive a +2 <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/glossary#TOC-Racial-Bonus\">racial bonus</a> on <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/perception\">Perception</a> checks.</li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 2px 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 15.2px;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 15.2px;\">Taunt:</strong>&nbsp;Kender have an uncanny insight into the motivations and characteristics of other races. They can use this insight to unleash a verbal barrage of sarcasm, insults, and crude comments that cause the targeted victims to lose their temper. Kender receive a +4 racial bonus on all Bluff checks to taunt someone. To taunt an opponent in combat, make a Bluff check opposed by a Sense Motive check by your target. If your Bluff check exceeds your target&rsquo;s Sense Motive check, your target is nettled by your taunts and suffers a -1 penalty on his attack rolls and AC until your next action. An enemy distracted by your taunts is likely to direct his next attack at you, but is under no compulsion to do so. Using the Bluff skill to taunt a foe requires a standard action, but does not provoke an attack of opportunity.</li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 2px 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 15.2px;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 15.2px;\">Weapon Familiarity</strong>: Kender are proficient with slings and treat any weapon with the word \"Kender\" in its name as a martial weapon.</li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"changes":[{"_id":"b17x28cb","formula":"2","operator":"add","target":"ability","subTarget":"dex","modifier":"racial","priority":0,"value":0},{"_id":"6qmpu6j7","formula":"2","operator":"add","target":"ability","subTarget":"cha","modifier":"racial","priority":0,"value":0},{"_id":"4qkk6fpi","formula":"-2","operator":"add","target":"ability","subTarget":"str","modifier":"racial","priority":0,"value":0},{"_id":"6nb88ge9","formula":"2","operator":"add","target":"skill","subTarget":"skill.per","modifier":"racial","priority":0,"value":0},{"_id":"bh8e3xbn","formula":"1","operator":"add","target":"savingThrows","subTarget":"allSa